The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: Mahindra Satyam is set to appoint Deloitte as its statutory auditor for 2009-10. An announcement to this effect is likely to be made this week after a meeting of the board of the company, sources said. Global auditing firm Deloitte had earlier shown interest to become the auditor of Satyam Computer Services, rebranded as Mahindra Satyam.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: The Orissa government will convene a meeting this week with Posco and ArcelorMittal to resolve issues such as land acquisition and mining leases. The meeting in Bhubaneswar is likely be held on October 23 and will be chaired by state chief secretary T.K. Mishra.                            
	 Gurgaon, Oct. 19: A youth died after being injured in a clash between two groups of workers of auto component firm Rico Auto over the issue of a strike, prompting the authorities to form a panel to resolve the dispute. The committee will be chaired by additional deputy commissioner Pushpender Chouhan.                             
	 Mumbai, Oct. 19: The Bombay Stock Exchange, the National Stock Exchange, forex, money, bullion, oils and oilseeds, grain, metal and cotton markets remained closed today on account of Bhai Dooj.                                                                                                                           
